COMPANY POLICY MANUAL
Version: 2026
Effective Date: January 1, 2026
Last Reviewed: December 2025

SECTION 1: ORGANIZATION OVERVIEW

Our organization is committed to operational excellence, security,
regulatory compliance, transparency, and employee well-being.
This policy manual governs internal conduct, system access,
data protection, and operational procedures.

All employees, contractors, interns, consultants, and executives
must comply with this manual. Violations may result in disciplinary
action including revocation of system access, suspension, or termination.

This manual is classified as Internal. Some sections contain
Confidential or Restricted information.

SECTION 2: ROLE DEFINITIONS

2.1 Intern
Interns are temporary employees assisting project teams.
Interns:
- May access internal documentation.
- May access assigned project repositories.
- May not access payroll, revenue data, or employee records.
- Must work under direct supervision of a Manager.

2.2 Employee
Employees are permanent or contractual staff members.
Employees:
- Have access to department documentation.
- May access internal dashboards.
- May request leave through HR systems.
- May not access executive financial forecasting reports.

2.3 Manager
Managers supervise teams and approve operational decisions.
Managers:
- Approve leave requests.
- Review team performance.
- Access departmental budget summaries.
- Cannot access company-wide acquisition strategies.

2.4 HR Personnel
HR manages employee lifecycle processes.
HR Personnel:
- Access employee personal data.
- Manage payroll systems.
- Maintain medical disclosures.
- Conduct disciplinary documentation.

2.5 Finance Team
Finance oversees budgeting and revenue operations.
Finance:
- Access financial statements.
- Manage tax compliance documentation.
- Maintain vendor payment records.
- Cannot access medical records.

2.6 Executive Leadership
Executives define strategic direction.
Executives:
- Access strategic financial planning.
- Access acquisition documents.
- Access audit reports.
- May override certain access restrictions under board authorization.

SECTION 3: ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL (RBAC) POLICY

Access is granted based on job role under the principle of least privilege.

All system permissions must:
- Be approved by department heads.
- Be reviewed quarterly.
- Be revoked immediately upon role change or termination.

Access Reviews:
- Conducted quarterly by IT and HR.
- Logged for compliance audit.
- Reviewed by executive leadership annually.

Classification Levels:
Public – Shareable externally.
Internal – Restricted to employees.
Confidential – Sensitive operational data.
Restricted – Highly sensitive executive/legal material.

SECTION 4: LEAVE POLICY

4.1 Annual Paid Leave

Full-time Employees are entitled to 20 days of paid leave annually.
Part-time Employees receive prorated leave based on working hours.
Unused leave may be carried forward up to a maximum of 10 days.
Carried-forward leave expires after 6 months.

Interns are entitled to 5 days of leave per internship cycle.
Managers and Executives may be eligible for extended leave
based on contractual agreements.

4.2 Sick Leave

Employees are entitled to 10 days of paid sick leave annually.
Medical certification is required for absences exceeding 3 consecutive days.
Unused sick leave does not carry forward.

4.3 Emergency Leave

Employees may request emergency leave for family or medical emergencies.
Approval is required from Manager and HR.
Documentation may be requested in certain cases.

4.4 Maternity and Paternity Leave

Maternity leave entitlement: 26 weeks paid leave.
Paternity leave entitlement: 15 days paid leave.
Extended unpaid leave may be granted upon HR approval.

4.5 Leave Approval Process

All leave must be:
- Requested via HR system.
- Approved by Manager.
- Recorded by HR.

Executives must notify the Board for leave exceeding 30 days.

4.6 Unauthorized Leave

Absence without approval for more than 3 consecutive days
may result in disciplinary action.

SECTION 5: INFORMATION SECURITY POLICY

5.1 Authentication and Password Policy

All employees must use multi-factor authentication (MFA).
Passwords must:
- Be at least 12 characters long.
- Include uppercase, lowercase, numeric, and special characters.
- Be changed every 90 days.
- Not reuse last 5 passwords.

Account lockout occurs after 5 failed login attempts.

5.2 Access Control Requirements

Access must:
- Be role-based.
- Be approved in writing.
- Be reviewed quarterly.

Privileged accounts must:
- Use separate login credentials.
- Not be used for daily operational tasks.
- Be monitored by security team.

5.3 Data Handling Policy

Confidential and Restricted documents:
- Must not be downloaded to personal devices.
- Must not be shared externally without authorization.
- Must be encrypted at rest and in transit.

Internal documents:
- May be shared within company systems.
- Must not be publicly distributed.

Public documents:
- May be shared externally after review.

5.4 Remote Work Security

Employees accessing systems remotely must:
- Use company VPN.
- Use company-issued devices.
- Avoid public Wi-Fi unless VPN is active.

Finance systems require IP-based access restrictions.
HR systems log all access events.

5.5 Incident Reporting

All suspected security incidents must be reported within 2 hours.
Security team will:
- Investigate breach.
- Document findings.
- Notify executive leadership if necessary.

Failure to report incidents may result in disciplinary action.

5.6 Data Breach Consequences

Unauthorized access to Restricted data:
- Immediate suspension of access.
- Internal investigation.
- Possible termination.
- Potential legal proceedings.

SECTION 6: DISCIPLINARY ACTIONS

Policy violations may result in:
- Warning letter.
- Access revocation.
- Suspension.
- Termination.

Repeated violations escalate penalties.
HR documents all disciplinary actions.

SECTION 7: DATA RETENTION POLICY

Employee records: retain 7 years.
Financial statements: retain 10 years.
Audit logs: retain 5 years.
Restricted legal documents: follow statutory law requirements.

Backup copies:
- Stored in encrypted storage.
- Retained for 3 years minimum.

END OF DOCUMENT
